      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2017-10-19T19:54:07.881+0000",
      "description": "If the drive that hosts the {{yarn.nodemanager.recovery.dir}} is broken then the entire NodeManager will not start.  Please improve this so that if the directory is not able to be created/accessed then the recovery portion of the NM is simply skipped and the NM continues to operate as normal.\r\n\r\nIt may also be beneficial to be able to define multiple directories, like YARN logging directories, so that if one drive fails, not all of the recovery data is lost.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://hadoop.apache.org/docs/r2.7.2/hadoop-yarn/hadoop-yarn-site/NodeManagerRestart.html",
